Issue: After having the calculator solve an equation, it can't properly solve again when another value for an addition equation is added
Steps to reproduce: 
	1. Solve an equation (don't clear the calculator) 
	2. Add 1 or more addition operators and values after the answer to create another equation
	3. Attempt to solve for the new quation, an incorrect answer will be outputted
Cause: The result of the previous equation is added to the first element of the input ArrayList to allow 
	   other operations to avoid this issue
Notes: -If I try to clear the input ArrayList at the end of the equals method, it becomes able to solve
	   equations one after the other, but if addition is used at all in any of those equations, it  
	   becomes unabpart of an le to solve properly again
	   -It appears to be trying to add together the previous equation and then the new value
	   of the next equation
	   -The input ArrayList size is being reset properly
	   -The first number entered after solving an equation is not added to the input ArrayList
Solution: The calculator now check to see if the current addition is the first time addition has been used since clearing.
		  If it has, add all the input ArrayList values together, if not, add them all except for the firt element.  
